title: #pnjpreps: Week 9 final scores
text: Week 9 prep football final scores Veronica Terefenko, vterefenko@pnj.com 10:57 p.m. CDT October 23, 2015 Pine Forest kicks off second half. Matt Foster/mrfoster@pnj.com So proud that Walton gather together with Northview team to pray together. Tracee Neese/Submitted Pine Forest Eagles host the Niceville Eagles. PFHS trailing at half-time 28-7. Bruce Graner/bgraner@pnj.com Washington makes it 14-0 over @PensacolaCHS, 2 min left in the half #pnjpreps. Ben Twingley/btwingley@pnj.com Slow moving first. Pensacola CHS vs Washington Wildcats. Ben Twingley/btwingley@pnj.com #pnjpreps @PensacolaCHS taking on #WashingtonHigh @BrianAchatzPNJ. Ben Twingley/btwingley@pnj.com Walton score 22-0 2 qtr, 9:08 time left. Tracee Neese/Submitted And here we go! Pine Forest vs Niceville starts now! Matt Foster/mrfoster@pnj.com Pine Forest ready to take the field .... Matt Foster/mrfoster@pnj.com Nice football field at Walton. Tracee Neese/Submitted Washington High's defensive linemen get ready for tonight's game vs Catholic. Bill Vilona/bvilona@pnj.com The annual award-winning Washington High band performs pregame. Bill Vilona/bvilona@pnj.com @wfhs_football Jags ready to hit the field. Brian Achatz/bachatz@pnj.com The @PensacolaCHS football team going thru final warmups before tonight's game vs Washington. Bill Vilona/bvilona@pnj.com Pensacola Catholic High School honors senior football players, cheerleaders, and student ambassadors at halftime. Bill Vilona/bvilona@pnj.com Quite a group as Pensacola Catholic High School honors its fall sport athletes, cheerleaders, band, and support groups. Bill Vilona/bvilona@pnj.com Getting ready for the National Anthem at Pine Forest. Matt Foster/mrfoster@pnj.com West Florida dads having some fun out here in PCB.
